|-
|[[File:en/Manual/Clear title.png]]
|'''[[en/Manual/Landscaping|Clear land]]'''
|6
|The dynamite tool is used to clear squares of either your own track you've built wrong, or anything that's in your way (well, not anything). Be aware that clicking on [[en/Manual/Stations|station]] will remove the whole [[en/Manual/Stations|station]] when there are no trains on it. For one-by-one removing [[en/Manual/Stations|station]] bits use the remove [R] tool

|-
|[[File:en/Manual/Build traindepot.png]]
|'''Build [[en/Manual/Depots|depot]]'''
|7
|Opens the [[en/Manual/Depots|depot]] build window for you to select a [[en/Manual/Depots|depot]] direction to build and what direction it will be facing.

|-
|[[File:en/Manual/Build waypoint.png]]
|'''Build [[en/Manual/Waypoints|waypoint]]'''
|8
|Allows you to build a [[en/Manual/Waypoints]] on/over a rail track.

|-
|[[File:en/Manual/Build station.png]]
|'''Build [[en/Manual/Stations|station]]'''
|9
|Opens the [[en/Manual/Stations|station]] build window for you to select a [[en/Manual/Stations|station]] size and direction to build.

|-
|[[File:en/Manual/Place signal.png]]
